cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper deals with using large-scale neuroscience data to regularize Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves using predictive models to denoise neural activity, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The regularization technique proposed in the paper involves penalizing intermediate representations that deviate from neural ones, which is a topic in the field of machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves improving model robustness in terms of adversarial attacks, which is a topic in the field of artificial intelligence and falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves using natural language processing techniques to analyze the results, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
